[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: ea76e639355e804b                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A critical security vulnerability has been detected in Apache Tika's file unpacking [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         functionality. The issue involves a file path traversal attack where malicious      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         archive entries containing path traversal sequences [1m([0me.g., `..[35m/../[0m`[1m)[0m can escape the [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         intended extraction directory. The vulnerability was discovered during fuzzing of   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the TikaCLI's embedded document extraction feature, specifically when processing    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         package/archive files that contain entries with manipulated path names designed to  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         write files outside the designated output directory.                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Issue Overview                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The security issue manifests as a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception with the  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         classification [32m"File path traversal"[0m. The exception is triggered when attempting to [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         write a file to the path                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[35m/tmp/expander-tmp16591270683959705981/output/q/r/s/t/../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`,      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which demonstrates a clear attempt to escape the intended output directory          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         structure using parent directory references [1m([0m`..[35m/../[0m`[1m)[0m.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Vulnerability Type                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This is a **Path Traversal vulnerability** [1m([0malso known as Directory Traversal or    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Zip Slip[1m)[0m, which allows an attacker to write files to arbitrary locations on the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         filesystem by manipulating file paths within archive entries. This type of          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         vulnerability can lead to:                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Overwriting critical system files                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Remote code execution [1m([0mif executable files are written to specific locations[1m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Information disclosure                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Denial of service                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Key Observations                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Detection Point**: The vulnerability was caught by the Jazzer sanitizer        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`FilePathTraversal.check`[1m)[0m at runtime, indicating that unsafe file operations were [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         being attempted but not properly validated by the application code itself.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Stack Trace Analysis**: The execution path shows:                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The issue originates in                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI$[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` at line [1;36m1111[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Processing flows through `[1;35mPackageParser.parseEntry[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mPackageParser.parseEntries[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The file output operation is initiated via                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mFilePathTraversal.processFileOutputStartHook[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Multiple parser layers are involved: `PackageParser` → `CompositeParser` →     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `AutoDetectParser`                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Attack Vector**: The malicious path `q/r/s/t/..[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         demonstrates that:                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The archive contains an entry with a relative path including parent directory  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         references                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The path is designed to navigate up from a deeply nested structure             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The final destination [1m([0m`jazzer-traversal`[1m)[0m would be written to a location two  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         directories above the expected output location                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Affected Component**: The vulnerability is specifically in the embedded        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         document extraction functionality [1m([0m`FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor`[1m)[0m within TikaCLI, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which is responsible for extracting and writing embedded files from package/archive [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         formats.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Areas for Investigation                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         To fully understand and address this vulnerability, the following components should [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be thoroughly examined:                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **TikaCLI.java**:                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Line [1;36m1111[0m in `[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - How file paths are constructed for embedded document extraction                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The complete `FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` class implementation              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Output directory handling and path validation logic                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **PackageParser.java**:                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mparseEntry[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method [1m([0mline [1;36m481[0m[1m)[0m - how individual archive entries are          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         processed                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mparseEntries[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method [1m([0mline [1;36m386[0m[1m)[0m - iteration and validation of multiple      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         entries                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35m_parse[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and `[1;35mparse[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` methods - initialization and setup of extraction      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parameters                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - How entry names/paths are retrieved from archive formats                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Path Construction and Validation**:                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Where and how output file paths are constructed from archive entry names       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - What [1m([0mif any[1m)[0m validation is performed on entry paths before file creation      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Whether paths are normalized or canonicalized before use                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - How the base output directory is established and enforced                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Supported Archive Formats**:                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Which archive formats are handled by PackageParser [1m([0mZIP, TAR, etc.[1m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Whether different formats have different path extraction behaviors             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Format-specific handling that might bypass validation                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **Configuration and Options**:                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Command-line options that control extraction behavior                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Whether there are security-related configuration options that should be        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         enforced                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Default behavior when extracting embedded documents                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis Summary[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical path traversal vulnerability in Apache Tika's file unpacking [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality. The issue exists in multiple locations where embedded documents are [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextracted to the filesystem without proper path validation.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability stems from insufficient path validation in [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.getOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method in TikaCLI.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1128[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1169[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The code uses `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which resolves [0m[32m".."[0m[39m and [0m[32m"."[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences but doesn't validate that the final resolved path remains within the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended extraction directory. When a malicious archive contains entries like [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m`, the path can escape the extraction directory.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Issues Identified[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **TikaCLI.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mLine [0m[1;36m1160[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: `new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, normalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` creates a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile path without validating containment[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mLine [0m[1;36m110[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: `[0m[1;35moutputDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` lacks path [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal validation[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **PackageParser.java**: Passes entry names from archives directly to extractors [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout validation[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Secure Pattern Reference[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase already contains the correct security pattern in [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileSystemFetcher.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath p = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfetchKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mp.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbasePath.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"fetchKey must resolve to be a descendant of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mthe 'basePath'"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis pattern must be adapted for the vulnerable code locations.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Patch TikaCLI.java - [0m[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.getOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaCLI.java`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Approach**: Add path traversal validation after constructing the output file path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut before returning it.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation Steps**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m After line [0m[1;36m1160[0m[39m where `File outputFile = new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, normalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis created, add validation logic.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Convert the File objects to Path objects and use canonical path resolution:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Convert `outputFile` to `Path` using `[0m[1;35moutputFile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Convert `extractDir` to `Path` using `[0m[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normalize and resolve both paths to their canonical forms[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate that the resolved output path starts with the resolved extract [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory path[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m The validation must handle the case where the file doesn't exist yet [0m[1;39m([0m[39msince [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwe're creating it[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use `[0m[1;35mPath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutput file [0m[1;39m([0m[39msince it doesn't exist yet[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for the extract directory [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich should exist[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate using `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to ensure containment[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39md[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m If validation fails, throw an `IOException` with a clear security message [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating path traversal was detected.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m This validation should occur BEFORE the directory existence check and UUID [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprepending logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1162[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1167[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that even if a malicious path would trigger [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe UUID prepending, it's still caught.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Preserved Logic**:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep all existing normalization steps [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull byte replacement, FilenameUtils [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations, prefix stripping, URL decoding[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintain the file existence check and UUID prepending functionality[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Preserve the extension handling and relationship ID logic[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep the fallback logic for null normalized names[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java - [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mMyEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-example/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/example/ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Approach**: Add path traversal validation after line [0m[1;36m110[0m[39m where the output path is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolved.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation Steps**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m After line [0m[1;36m110[0m[39m where `Path outputFile = [0m[1;35moutputDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called, add [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Since this code uses the modern Path API, the validation is more [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstraightforward:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normalize the outputFile path[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normalize the outputDir path  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate that the normalized output path starts with the normalized output [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory path[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m For this example code, we can use a slightly different approach since parent [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectories are created later:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on both paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich doesn't require file existence[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure the normalized output path starts with the normalized output directory[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents traversal attempts before any filesystem operations[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39md[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m If validation fails, throw an `IOException` with a security message.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Preserved Logic**:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep the file name normalization [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull byte replacement, prefix stripping[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintain the file existence check and UUID prepending[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Preserve the extension detection logic[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep the directory creation and file copy operations[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Details[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**For TikaCLI.java validation logic**:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter line [0m[1;36m1160[0m[39m:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Convert File objects to Path objects[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Get the absolute normalized path of the output file [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent must exist[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Get the real path of the extract directory[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Check if output path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its parent's real path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m starts with extract directory's[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreal path[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. If not, throw IOException with message: [0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mresource: "[0m[39m + name[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Ensure this validation occurs before any mkdir operations related to this [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecific file[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**For ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java validation logic**:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter line [0m[1;36m110[0m[39m:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Normalize the outputFile path using [0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Normalize the outputDir path using [0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Check if normalized output path starts with normalized output directory[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. If not, throw IOException with message: [0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mresource: "[0m[39m + name[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Error Handling Strategy[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBoth patches must:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throw `IOException` [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready in the method signatures[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Include the suspicious name in the error message for security logging[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Not catch or suppress the exception [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlet it propagate for security visibility[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Log at WARN or ERROR level before throwing[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe existing try-catch block in [0m[1;35mTikaCLI.parseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1119[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1125[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcatch and log these security exceptions, which is acceptable behavior for the CLI [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtool.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Leverages Existing Secure Pattern**: The fix adapts the proven secure pattern [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom FileSystemFetcher, maintaining consistency with existing Tika security [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpractices.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Code Changes**: The validation is added as a focused security check [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout restructuring the existing logic flow.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Functionality**: All current path normalization, file [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexistence handling, and extraction features remain intact.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: The validation occurs after all normalization steps, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproviding a final security gate before filesystem operations.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Clear Security Boundary**: The fix establishes a clear security boundary - no [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextracted file can exist outside the designated extraction directory.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Maintains Compatibility**: All valid archive entries will continue to extract [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Preserves File Naming**: The UUID prepending for duplicate files still works[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Keeps Subdirectory Support**: Valid subdirectories [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[32m"subdir/file.txt"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare still created[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **No Breaking Changes**: Existing tests should pass [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexcept if they rely on [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsecure behavior[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Blocks Path Traversal**: The canonical path validation prevents `[0m[32m"../../"[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences from escaping the extraction directory[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Catches Attack Vector**: The specific fuzzer input [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"q/r/s/t/../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[39m` will be blocked by the `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Validates Before Operations**: The check occurs before directory creation [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1105[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and file writing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1111[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Provides Clear Errors**: Security exceptions include the malicious path for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maudit logging[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Symbolic Link Handling**: [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: Symbolic links in the extraction directory might cause validation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missues[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Use `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for extractDir which resolves symlinks, and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for the output path construction[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Cross-Platform Path Handling**:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: Different path separators on Windows vs Unix[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Path API handles platform differences automatically; existing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFilenameUtils normalization already addresses this[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance**:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: Additional path resolution adds minimal overhead[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: The overhead is negligible compared to I/O operations and existing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalization steps[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Existing Archives**:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: Archives with legitimate absolute paths or parent references will[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe rejected[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: This is desired security behavior; the prefix stripping [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1151[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1154[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already handles absolute paths, so legitimate cases should work[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe FileSystemFetcher implementation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m provides the reference pattern. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis same validation approach is also used in:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` helper method in FileSystemFetcher [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar containment validation patterns exist throughout the Tika codebase for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity-sensitive operations[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy implementing this fix strategy, we address the critical path traversal [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability while maintaining full backward compatibility with legitimate archive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction use cases.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         +                throw new [1;35mIOException[0m[1m([0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mresource: "[0m + name[1m)[0m;                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +            [1m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                      if [1m([0m[1;35mFiles.exists[0m[1m([0moutputFile[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         +                normalizedOutput = [1;35moutputFile.toAbsolutePath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                if [1m([0m![1;35mnormalizedOutput.startsWith[0m[1m([0mnormalizedOutputDir[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m           [2m                [0m
