[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: ea76e639355e804b                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue reveals a critical security vulnerability [1m([0mFile path traversal[1m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         detected during fuzzing of the Apache Tika codebase. The vulnerability occurs when  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         extracting embedded documents, where a malicious archive entry with a path          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         containing traversal sequences [1m([0me.g., `..[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`[1m)[0m can escape the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         intended extraction directory. The patch attempt adds path validation logic to      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         prevent such traversals in two locations: `TikaCLI.java` and                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java`. However, the compilation failed due to unhandled       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `IOException` declarations, indicating the patch requires modification to properly  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         handle exceptions according to the method signatures.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Initial Issue Analysis                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The security issue manifests as a file path traversal vulnerability with the        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         following characteristics:                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Vulnerability Type**: File path traversal attack [1m([0mCritical security issue[1m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Trigger Point**: The vulnerability is detected when                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FilePathTraversal.processFileOutputStartHook` validates a file path during         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         embedded document extraction                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Malicious Path**: The attack uses a relative path                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[35m/tmp/expander-tmp16591270683959705981/output/q/r/s/t/../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m` which [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         contains directory traversal sequences [1m([0m`..[35m/../[0m`[1m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Call Stack**: The issue originates from:                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `[1;35mTikaCLI.FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` at line [1;36m1111[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Through the package parser chain: `[1;35mPackageParser.parseEntry[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` →               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mPackageParser.parseEntries[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` → `[1;35mPackageParser._parse[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Eventually reaching the CompositeParser and AutoDetectParser layers            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The stack trace indicates that when Tika processes package files [1m([0mZIP, TAR, or      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         similar archives[1m)[0m, it extracts embedded documents without properly validating that  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the resolved file paths remain within the designated extraction directory.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Patch Attempt Description                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch introduces path traversal protection at two critical locations:           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         #### [1;36m1[0m. TikaCLI.java [1m([0mlines [1;36m1158[0m-[1;36m1208[0m[1m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch modifies the `FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` class's file creation logic: [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **First validation block [1m([0mafter line [1;36m1160[0m[1m)[0m**:                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Converts the output file to an absolute, normalized path                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Retrieves the real path of the extraction directory                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Validates the parent directory path:                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - If the parent exists, resolves it to a real path and checks if it starts with   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the extraction path                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - If the parent doesn't exist, uses normalized paths for validation               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Validates the final output path itself to ensure it starts with the extraction    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         path                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Throws `IOException` with a descriptive message if path traversal is detected     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **Second validation block [1m([0mafter line [1;36m1193[0m[1m)[0m**:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - After prepending UUID to handle existing files, re-validates the modified path    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Performs the same `[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` check on normalized paths                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Throws `IOException` if validation fails after UUID modification                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         #### [1;36m2[0m. ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java [1m([0mlines [1;36m108[0m-[1;36m128[0m[1m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch adds similar protection to the example code:                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **First validation [1m([0mafter line [1;36m110[0m[1m)[0m**:                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Normalizes both the output file path and output directory                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Uses `[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to verify the output file is within the directory             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Throws `IOException` for detected traversals                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         **Second validation [1m([0mafter line [1;36m121[0m[1m)[0m**:                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Re-validates after UUID prepending for duplicate file handling                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Applies the same normalized path comparison                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Compilation Errors                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch compilation failed with two specific errors in `TikaCLI.java`:            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Line [1;36m1186[0m**: `unreported exception java.io.IOException; must be caught or      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         declared to be thrown`                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Line [1;36m1204[0m**: `unreported exception java.io.IOException; must be caught or      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         declared to be thrown`                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         These errors occur because:                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Line [1;36m1186[0m corresponds to the first path validation block where                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mFiles.exists[0m[1m([0mparentPath[1m)[0m` and subsequent operations can throw `IOException`        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Line [1;36m1204[0m corresponds to the second validation block after UUID prepending        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The method containing this code does not declare `IOException` in its throws      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         clause, nor does the patch wrap these operations in proper exception handling       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The existing code structure shows that the method calls                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.toRealPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` which can throw `IOException`, but the patch's   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         additional validation logic introduces new `IOException` throwing points without    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         proper exception handling.                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Areas Requiring Further Investigation                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Method Signature Analysis**: The method containing the patched code needs      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         examination to determine:                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Current exception handling strategy [1m([0mwhat exceptions are already               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         declared/caught[1m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Whether the method should propagate `IOException` or handle it internally      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Impact on calling code if method signature changes                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Existing Path Handling**: Investigation of how the codebase currently handles  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         file paths:                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review of `[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` usage and its security guarantees        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - URL decoding logic around line [1;36m1156[0m-[1;36m1159[0m and its potential for introducing     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         traversal characters                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The `normalizedName` variable construction and its validation                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Edge Cases**: Analysis of scenarios that might bypass validation:              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Symbolic links handling and `[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` behavior                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Windows vs Unix path separator handling                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Case sensitivity considerations                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Unicode and special character handling in file names                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. **Consistent Protection**: Verification that all file extraction paths are       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         protected:                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review of other parsers that extract files [1m([0mnot just PackageParser[1m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Check if similar vulnerabilities exist in other extraction points              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Validate that the example code in `ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java` matches          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         production code patterns                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. **Error Handling Strategy**: Understanding the appropriate response to path      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         traversal detection:                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Whether to fail silently, log warnings, or throw exceptions                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Impact on batch processing and user experience                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Existing error handling patterns in the codebase                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFile path traversal: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/expander-tmp16591270683959705981/output/q/r/s/t/../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFilePathTraversal.j[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1160[0m[39m:            File outputFile = new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, normalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1161[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mif[0m[39m file already exists, prepend uuid[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1162[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35moutputFile.exists[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1163[0m[39m:                String fileName = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1169[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/pipes/fetcher/fs/FileSystemFetcher.jav[0m[1;92ma:64[0m[39m-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:    static boolean [0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath root, Path descendant[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mdescendant.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mroot.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the evaluation report and code snippets, I've identified the core [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue and the appropriate fix strategy:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method in `TikaCLI.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1128[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m does not validate that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolved file paths remain within the extraction directory. Malicious archive [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries with path traversal sequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can escape [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe intended extraction directory.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why the Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The patch attempted to use `[0m[1;35mFiles.exists[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on paths that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdon't exist yet[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method signature didn't declare `throws IOException`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. This caused compilation errors at lines [0m[1;36m1186[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m1204[0m[39m where IOExceptions could [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe thrown but weren't properly declared[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Insights from Code Analysis[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **FileSystemFetcher pattern** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows the correct validation [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproach using `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that works on [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon-existent paths[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Method signatures**: `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already declares `throws IOException`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso propagating IOException from `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is acceptable[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Two validation points needed**: After initial file creation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1160[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter UUID prepending for duplicates [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1166[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java**: Has the same vulnerability and uses Path API, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaking it easier to fix[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Modify TikaCLI.java[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1.1[0m[39m: Update `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method signature**[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change from: `private File [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name, Metadata metadata, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMediaType contentType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change to: `private File [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name, Metadata metadata, MediaType [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontentType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1.2[0m[39m: Add first validation block after line [0m[1;36m1160[0m[39m**[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter `File outputFile = new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, normalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, add:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that the resolved path is within the extraction directory[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath outputPath = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath extractPath = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35moutputPath.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded resource: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1.3[0m[39m: Add second validation block after line [0m[1;36m1166[0m[39m**[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter the UUID-prepended file creation:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Revalidate after UUID prepending[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutputPath = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35moutputPath.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded resource after UUID [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mprepend: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Key differences from failed patch:**[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - works on [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon-existent paths[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Properly declares `throws IOException` in method signature[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Simpler validation logic without checking parent existence separately[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Directly compares normalized absolute paths[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Modify ExtractEmbeddedFiles.java[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2.1[0m[39m: Add first validation block after line [0m[1;36m110[0m[39m**[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter `Path outputFile = [0m[1;35moutputDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, add:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that the resolved path is within the output directory[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath normalizedOutput = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath normalizedOutputDir = [0m[1;35moutputDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mnormalizedOutput.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedOutputDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded resource: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2.2[0m[39m: Add second validation block after line [0m[1;36m114[0m[39m**[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter UUID-prepended path creation:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Revalidate after UUID prepending[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalizedOutput = [0m[1;35moutputFile.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mnormalizedOutput.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedOutputDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Path traversal detected in embedded resource after UUID [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mprepend: "[0m[39m + name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Note:** No signature change needed here as `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already declares [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`throws IOException`[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Uses proven pattern**: Follows the `[0m[1;35mFileSystemFetcher.isDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pattern [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready in the Tika codebase[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Handles non-existent paths**: `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` works on paths that don't exist [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39myet, unlike `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Minimal signature changes**: Only changes `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` signature, which [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis private and called only from `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that already handles IOException[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Consistent validation**: Both file creation points are validated the same way[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Clear error messages**: Throws IOException with descriptive messages about [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath traversal detection[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Maintains path normalization**: All existing path cleaning [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull byte removal,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprefix stripping, URL decoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains intact[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves UUID prepending**: Duplicate file handling with UUID prefixes works [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly as before[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Compatible with test cases**: [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Absolute paths are still stripped by existing logic before validation[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate relative paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39msubdirectories[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pass validation[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - UUID prepending for duplicates works correctly[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Exception handling**: IOException propagates to existing try-catch in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which logs and continues[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents path traversal**: Validates that normalized paths stay within [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction directory[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Fixes compilation errors**: Properly declares IOException in method signature[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Handles edge cases**: Works with non-existent paths, duplicate files, and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvarious path formats[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Security-focused**: Rejects malicious paths before any file system operations [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccur[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Breaking change for malicious archives**: Archives with path traversal entries[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill now fail[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is the intended behavior to prevent security [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerabilities[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Exception handling**: IOException now thrown from `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already has try-catch that logs and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance impact**: Additional path normalization operations[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Minimal impact; normalization is already done by [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **FileSystemFetcher** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Uses same [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pattern[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **UnrarParser** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m148[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows awareness of path traversal concerns in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive extraction[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **FSUtil.resolveRelative** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m202[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Validates absolute paths but doesn't[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck traversal - this fix adds the missing traversal check[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
